<TITLE> SC halts Mamun's bail in 4 extortion cases </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 27 (bdnews24.com)--The Supreme Court on Tuesday halted bail until Nov 1 to controversial businessman Giasuddin Al Mamun in four extortion cases. The five-member Appellate Division bench headed by chief justice M M Ruhul Amin also ordered him to file leave to appeal against the High Court order by the period. The High Court on Oct 8 granted Mamun the bails. The Appellate Division chamber judge Justice Mohammed Mozammel Hossain stayed the HC ruling unitl Oct 18 on a government appeal the next day. Barrister Rafique-Ul Haque stood for Mamun, a close friend and business partner of opposition chief Khaleda Zia's elder son Tarique Rahman. The Appellate Division on Monday briefly halted Mamun's bail granted by the High Court in a tax evasion case. Joint forces arrested Mamun on Jan 30, 2007. bdnew
